What is Javascript?
JavaScript is a lightweight, cross-platform, single-threaded, and interpreted compiled programming language. 
It is also known as the scripting language for webpages.
It is well-known for the development of web pages, and many non-browser environments also use it.

What is hoisting in Javascript?
Hoisting in Javascript is a behaviour in which a function or a variable can be used before declaration.
Only declarations are hoisted , initilizations are not hoisted.

What are the scopes in JS?
scopes determine the accessibility of vauables.
JS has 2 scopes
1.Global scope
